criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Adults older than 60;

          2. Competent to provide informed consent;

          3. Undergoing major elective cardiac surgery requiring a minimum stay of 2 days
             postoperatively.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Unable to provide informed consent;

          2. Undergoing neurosurgical procedures;

          3. Preoperative delirium;

          4. Unable to participate adequately in delirium screening including those who are blind,
             deaf, illiterate or not fluent English;

          5. History of intraoperative awareness

          6. Planned surgery (planned prior to index surgery) occurring within five days after
             index surgery
